article.headline: Eastern Michigan 74, North Dakota State 66
article.story: YPSILANTI, Mich. (AP) -- Carlos Medlock scored 14 of his 23 points in the second half Wednesday and Eastern Michigan won its third straight, a 74-66 victory over North Dakota State. Brett Winkelman had 16 points and Mike Nelson added 15 for the Bison (8-6), who lost their second straight. The Eagles (5-8) were 15-for-24 from the field in the first half and took control with an early 15-0 run. North Dakota State went almost seven minutes without scoring during the decisive streak and trailed 40-25 at the half. Eastern Michigan cooled off in the second half but the Bison never got close enough to threaten their hosts. North Dakota State outrebounded the Eagles 31-27 but committed 15 turnovers that led to 15 points. Jarred Axon came off the bench to score 14 points for the Eagles. Ben Woodside had 14 points and six assists for the Bison, who also got 10 rebounds from Andre Smith.
